  "prompt": "How can I use the Wi-Fi on my windows phone (wp8.1) in BHU (hostels, departments, library)?",
  "response": "To use Wi-Fi in BHU (Banaras Hindu University) on your Windows Phone (WP8.1), follow these steps:\n\n1. Campus Wi-Fi Configuration:\n- Contact BHU's IT department or network administrator\n- Get the specific Wi-Fi network credentials (SSID and password)\n\n2. Wi-Fi Settings on Windows Phone:\n- Go to Settings\n- Tap on \"Wi-Fi\"\n- Turn Wi-Fi on\n- Select the BHU network\n- Enter the provided username and password\n\n3. Additional Tips:\n- Ensure your device's software is updated\n- Check if you need any specific authentication settings\n- Verify network compatibility with your device\n\n4. Potential Authentication Methods:\n- Some campus networks might require:\n  - 802.1x authentication\n  - Specific login portal\n  - MAC address registration\n\n5. Troubleshooting:\n- Restart your phone\n- Verify credentials\n- Check with IT support if connection fails\n\nRecommendation: Directly contact BHU's IT support for precise configuration details specific to their network setup.",
